17 11:10:08','',127,'http://wp.dev.knotel.com/index.php/2017/08/17/127-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(129,1,'2017-08-17 11:10:53','2017-08-17 11:10:53','<p class=\"gtm-black\" style=\"color: rgb(187, 159, 125); font-size: 32px; text-transform: uppercase;\">BROKER PARTNERSHIP PROGRAM</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"gtm-black\">TERMS OF SERVICE</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nSubject to the terms and conditions of these rules, Knotel will compensate individuals or entities for each qualified member introduction that leads to the execution of a Knotel membership agreement (“<b>Membership Agreement</b>”).\r\n</p>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h4 class=\"gtm-black\">A. QUALIFIED INTRODUCTION </h4>\r\n    <p>\r\nSubject to these terms and conditions, for any entity (the “<b>Introduced Entity</b>) to be considered a qualified introduction, such Introduced Entity must:\r\n    </p>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>\r\nsign a membership contract for workspaces in a “Knotel” no later than <b>90 days</b> from the date of Submission (as defined below);\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li>not be current or previous members of Knotel;</li>\r\n        <li>\r\nnot have previously contacted Knotel for a membership or attended a Knotel event or otherwise been submitted by another party prior to your Submission in the <b>60 days</b> prior to your Submission;\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li>not be an affiliate (i.e. a subsidiary, parent, or under common control) of the entity providing the introduction; and</li>\r\n        <li>In the event an Introduced Entity is introduced more than once, we will honor the Submission we receive earliest, unless an exclusive agreement exists between the Introduced Entity and one of the entities providing the introduction.</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h4 class=\"gtm-black\">B. PROCESS </h4><b>Submission (“Submission”)</b>\r\n    <p>\r\nTo be eligible to receive the fees (“<b>Fee</b>”) described in these rules, you must accept these terms and conditions. Introductions may be submitted by completing the “Broker Introduction” form submission at <a href=\"http://wp.dev.knotel.com/index.php/tenant-reps/\" style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">knotel.com/brokers</a> and entering all required information:\r\n\r\n    </p>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li>Your first and last name</li>\r\n        <li>Your email address &amp; phone number</li>\r\n        <li>Introduced Entity Name</li>\r\n        <li>Name of the primary contact for the entity you are representing</li>\r\n        <li>Valid email address for the primary contact at the entity you are representing</li>\r\n        <li>Team Size (# of Seats)</li>\r\n        <li>Projected Move-In Date</li>\r\n        <li>Introduced Entity’s Knotel location of interest</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    <p>You must complete a separate Submission for each Introduced Entity. You may only complete a single Submission per potential member company that you would like to introduce. Incomplete Submissions will result in ineligibility from collecting Fees until a complete Submission is received. You further represent that the Introduced Entity has approved (verbally or in writing) your filling out the Submission on its behalf.</p><b>Contact with Introduced Entity</b>\r\n    <p>\r\nFollowing a complete Submission, we will contact the Introduced Entity confirming our receipt of the Submission unless otherwise instructed to contact you first. By agreeing to these terms and conditions, you hereby represent that you have obtained valid consent from the Introduced Entity to send the Introduced Entity’s contact information to Knotel for the purpose of participating in the Broker Program (the “<b>Program</b>”) with Knotel described in these Terms and Conditions. The Introduced Entity will have the opportunity to inform us that (a) it does not desire a Knotel membership and/or (b) it has not given authorization to you in connection with the introduction. If the Introduced Entity informs us that it has not given authorization to you, you will not be eligible for the Fee even if such Introduced Entity becomes a Qualified introduction. If the Introduced Entity does not so inform us, you may continue to receive email communications. Referral submissions that do not adhere to the procedures outlined above will not be recognized as valid by Knotel or our Growth Team and will not be processed for payment.\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h4 class=\"gtm-black\">C. FEE(S)</h4>\r\n    <p>Subject to these terms and conditions, Knotel will pay you for qualified introductions a Fee equal to a percentage of the membership fee agreed to in the initial Membership Agreement and paid in full by the Introduced Entity and received in full by Knotel, in accordance with the Fee structure in the table below.</p><b>For Agreements of less than 12 months:</b>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Time Period</th>\r\n            <th>Fee</th>\r\n            <th>Payment Timing</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Months 1-3:</td>\r\n            <td>10%</td>\r\n            <td>Upfront Payment</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Months 4 - 12:</td>\r\n            <td>10%</td>\r\n            <td>Paid Monthly (no payments will be made after Month 12 for commitments of less than 12 months)</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </table><b>For Agreements of 12 - 36 Months:</b>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Time Period</th>\r\n            <th>Fee</th>\r\n            <th>Payment Timing</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Months 1-12:</td>\r\n            <td>10%</td>\r\n            <td>Upfront Payment</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Months 13 - 36:</td>\r\n            <td>2%</td>\r\n            <td>Paid Monthly</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </table><b>Expansion:</b>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Time Period</th>\r\n            <th>Fee</th>\r\n            <th>Payment Timing</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Months 1-12:</td>\r\n            <td>10%</td>\r\n            <td>Paid Monthly</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </table><b>Renewal Terms:</b>\r\n    <table>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <th>Time Period</th>\r\n            <th>Fee</th>\r\n            <th>Payment Timing</th>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td>Months 1-24:</td>\r\n            <td>2%</td>\r\n            <td>Paid Monthly for up to 24 months of renewal term.</td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n    </table>\r\n    <p>Because Knotel Membership Agreements may have a term as short as one (1) month, Knotel can provide no assurances regarding how long the term of any particular Membership Agreements may be. If the Membership Agreements is terminated early, you will only receive a Fee for the duration of the Introduced Entity’s membership contract term. In the event that the termination of a Knotel membership contract results in an overpayment of Fees by Knotel, the amount equal to the original prepaid Fees less the adjusted Fees due to the shortened term of the Knotel membership contract must be promptly returned to Knotel. Under no circumstances will Fees be paid after termination of the Introduced Entity’s Knotel Membership Agreement.</p><b>Renewal</b>\r\n    <p>A “Renewal Agreement” is a Membership Agreement that has been resigned by a current Knotel member for a new commitment term pertaining to the same space as such member’s initial Membership Agreements. Renewals do not apply to members with month to month agreements. For each successful client-member Renewal, Knotel will pay you a Fee equal to a percentage of the membership fee agreed to in the renewal Membership Agreements and paid in full by the Introduced Entity and received in full by Knotel, in accordance with the Fee structure in the table above.</p><b>Expansion &amp; Reduction </b>\r\n    <p>\r\nIf the Introduced Entity takes additional dedicated desks or office space at either the same Knotel location or a new Knotel location (“<b>Expansion</b>”) during the term of its Knotel membership contract, Fees on such Expansion shall be calculated by determining the amount of time left on such entity’s Knotel membership contract and then following the schedule in the table above. Decreases in the membership fee due to reducing the number of dedicated desks or office space will proportionally decrease the Fee. In the event that such a reduction results in an overpayment of Fees by Knotel, at Knotel’s option, the amount equal to the original prepaid Fees for the period less the adjusted Fees due to such reduction for the period will be either (i) credited against future prepayments of Fees, if applicable or (ii) promptly returned to Knotel.\r\n    </p><b>Limitations on Referral Fees Relating to an Introduced Entity</b>\r\n    <p>Fees are paid for membership fees only, not any other fees paid by the member. Fees will also be adjusted to reflect the total membership fee less any discounts agreed to by the Introduced Entity.</p><b>Payment</b>\r\n    <p>\r\nBy agreeing to these terms you accept that Knotel will pay Fees owed in reference to the Introduced Entity\'s membership fees, net of any discounts, to the banking information provided by you. You will receive an email confirmation, from Knotel detailing the Fees, and you agree that such email shall serve as a valid invoice and record of transaction. If you do not receive such an email, please contact<a href=\"mailto:brokers@knotel.com\">brokers@knotel.com</a>. All disputes regarding fees must be communicated in writing to <a href=\"mailto:brokers@knotel.com\">brokers@knotel.com</a> or in response to such email received from Knotel within 24 hours. Failure to respond to the Knotel confirmation email within such time period shall act as a waiver of any dispute regarding Fees described in such email.\r\n\r\n    </p>\r\n    <p>The payment of any lump sum Fees (except in the case of an Expansion), will be made within seven (7) days of execution of the Introduced Entity’s Membership Agreement; provided that if any entity introduced by you (x) fails to pay in full the Refundable Services Retainer due under such Introduced Entity’s Membership Agreement subsequent to its execution of the Membership Agreement or (y) terminates the Membership Agreement prior to the Start Date specified therein, then Fees for all subsequent Introduced Entities shall be paid on the later of (x) the Start Date pursuant to the Membership Agreement; and (y) the Introduced Entity’s payment and our receipt in full of the Refundable Services Retainer under such Introduced Entity’s Membership Agreement. In the case of an Expansion, the payment of any lump sum Fees will be made within seven (7) days of the Introduced Entity’s signing of a Membership Agreement for such Expansion. Monthly Fees will be paid no later than one month following each full calendar month of fully paid occupancy by the Introduced Entity’s company.</p><b>Communication</b>\r\n    <p>\r\nAll communication regarding the amount of referral fees and the schedule of payments shall come from the Knotel Growth team. Any questions or concerns regarding these terms and the referral program should be addressed to the Knotel Growth team at <a href=\"mailto:brokers@knotel.com\">brokers@knotel.com</a>. While you may receive unofficial contact from other Knotel departments regarding your referral, please be advised that any such communication shall be considered advisory only, any information provided to you by such other team may not be correct or valid, and no determinations, especially regarding validity of a referral, made by such other team may be considered binding. The Knotel Growth team shall be responsible for the final determinations regarding all referrals made pursuant to the Knotel Referral Program.\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h4 class=\"gtm-black\">D. MISCELLANEOUS</h4>\r\n    <p>\r\n“<b>Knotel</b>” for the purposes of these terms and conditions is Knotel, Inc., a D