n of interest</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    <p>You must complete a separate Submission for each Introduced Entity. You may only complete a single Submission per potential member company that you would like to introduce. Incomplete Submissions will result in ineligibility from collecting Fees until a complete Submission is received. You further represent that the Introduced Entity has approved (verbally or in writing) your filling out the Submission on its behalf.</p><b>Contact with Introduced Entity</b>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <!-- react-text: 271 -->Following a complete Submission, we will contact the Introduced Entity confirming our receipt of the Submission unless otherwise instructed to contact you first. By agreeing to these terms and conditions, you hereby represent that you have obtained valid consent from the Introduced Entity to send the Introduced Entity’s contact information to Knotel for the purpose of participating in the Broker Program (the “\r\n        <!-- /react-text --><b>Program</b>\r\n        <!-- react-text: 273 -->”) with Knotel described in these Terms and Conditions. The Introduced Entity will have the opportunity to inform us that (a) it does not desire a Knotel membership and/or (b) it has not given authorization to you in connection with the introduction. If the Introduced Entity informs us that it has not given authorization to you, you will not be eligible for the Fee even if such Introduced Entity becomes a Qualified introduction. If the Introduced Entity does not so inform us, you may continue to receive email communications. Referral submissions that do not adhere to the procedures outlined above will not be recognized as valid by Knotel or our Growth Team and will not be processed for payment.\r\n        <!-- /react-text -->\r\n    </p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n    <h4 class=\"gtm-black\">C. FEE(S)</h4>\r\n    <p>Subject to these terms and conditions, Knotel will pay you for qualified introductions a Fee equal to a percentage of the membership