 in full by Knotel, in accordance with the Fee structure in the table above.</p><b>Expansion &amp; Reduction </b>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <!-- react-text: 330 -->If the Introduced Entity takes additional dedicated desks or office space at either the same Knotel location or a new Knotel location (“\r\n        <!-- /react-text --><b>Expansion</b>\r\n        <!-- react-text: 332 -->”) during the term of its Knotel membership contract, Fees on such Expansion shall be calculated by determining the amount of time left on such entity’s Knotel membership contract and then following the schedule in the table above. Decreases in the membership fee due to reducing the number of dedicated desks or office space will proportionally decrease the Fee. In the event that such a reduction results in an overpayment of Fees by Knotel, at Knotel’s option, the amount equal to the original prepaid Fees for the period less the adjusted Fees due to such reduction for the period will be either (i) credited against future prepayments of Fees, if applicable or (ii) promptly returned to Knotel.\r\n        <!-- /react-text -->\r\n    </p><b>Limitations on Referral Fees Relating to an Introduced Entity</b>\r\n    <p>Fees are paid for membership fees only, not any other fees paid by the member. Fees will also be adjusted to reflect the total membership fee less any discounts agreed to by the Introduced Entity.</p><b>Payment</b>\r\n    <p>\r\n        <!-- react-text: 337 -->By agreeing to these terms you accept that Knotel will pay Fees owed in reference to the Introduced Entity\'s membership fees, net of any discounts, to the banking information provided by you. You will receive an email confirmation, from Knotel detailing the Fees, and you agree that such email shall serve as a valid invoice and record of transaction. If you do not receive such an email, please contact\r\n        <!-- /react-text --><a href=\"mailto:brokers@knotel.com\">brokers@knotel.com</a>\r\n        <!-- react-text: 339 -->. All